The statement references "Last December" as when the Committee indicated its asset purchase guidance, and mentions the specific amounts of $80 billion/month in Treasuries and $40 billion/month in agency MBS. This QE program was announced in December 2020. The phrase "Last December" suggests this statement was issued in early 2021. The FOMC meetings in 2021 were in January, March, April/May, June, July, September, November, and December.

The language "Last December" most naturally refers to a meeting shortly after December 2020, likely the January 2021 or March 2021 meeting. This type of reference language ("Last December, the Committee indicated...") was used in the January 2021 and March 2021 statements. By June 2021, they started discussing tapering more actively. The January 2021 meeting (January 26-27) would be the first meeting after December 2020 where this language appeared.

